# Data Flow and Validation

Database data flow must stay on the server and use typed Zod validation.

- Retrieve database data in server components.
- Perform database inserts, updates, and deletes in server actions.
- Validate all data passed to server actions with Zod before using it.
- Give server action inputs explicit TypeScript types; do not type server action inputs as `FormData`.
- Prefer deriving TypeScript input types from Zod schemas when practical, so runtime validation and static types stay aligned.
